 A 27-year-old man, Zuko Ntshantshi, will spend the next five years in prison after he was found guilty of murder and sentenced by the Centane Regional Magistrate's Court on Tuesday. "It is alleged that the accused stabbed to death 24-year-old Mhlangabezi Yeyani," described police spokseperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The deceased was stabbed on 02 May 2014, at about 01:05, at Msengeni Location, Khantolo Village, Centane. "The deceased died immediately at the scene." The motive for the murder remains unclear to this day. 